message:
{{#is_alert}}
@pagerduty-NeuroQuest-Backend

**The strict GDPR and/or IAP device-signature gates are rejecting real (active) installs.**

More than the warning/critical threshold of `device_signature_strict:missing|invalid|id_mismatch` (privacy export/erasure) and/or `iap_device_auth:missing|invalid|id_mismatch` (purchase entitlements) rejections from device-aware clients (`@extra.active_install:true`) fired in the last 15 minutes. The normal baseline is ~0 — a spike means a change has started wrongly locking legitimate members out of data export, erasure, or purchases.

**MITIGATION — these paths do NOT honor DEVICE_AUTH_SOFT_MODE:**
Unlike the general per-:id gate, `requireDeviceSignatureStrict` (GDPR export/erasure in `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/app-user.ts`) and `requireUserOrDevice` (IAP entitlements in `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/iap.ts`) INTENTIONALLY ignore the soft-mode escape hatch — regulated data and purchase grants must never flow through the rollback path. Setting `DEVICE_AUTH_SOFT_MODE=1` will NOT stop these 401s.
1. **Roll back / revert the regression directly.** Redeploy the last-known-good build of `api-server` (or revert the offending change to the gate or the mobile signer). There is no flag-only mitigation for these two paths — fixing the code/signature is the only path to recovery.
2. Confirm recovery: this monitor should recover within ~15m as the active-install rejection count drops back toward 0.
3. Investigate the regression: a recent deploy touching `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/app-user.ts` (strict gate), `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/iap.ts` (IAP gate), `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/deviceAuth.ts` (shared verify), or the mobile signer in `artifacts/neuro-quest-mobile/lib/userAuth.ts`.
{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_recovery}}
Strict/IAP device-signature active-install rejection rate is back below threshold.
{{/is_recovery}}
